<heading id="D0C37C0CFFD0FF8319EB61C850ED2AA1" bold="true" box="[136,251,1758,1784]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF8319EB61C850ED2AA1" bold="true" box="[136,251,1758,1784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8BCB60FFD0FF8319EB601553E82B3C" blockId="1.[136,1451,1758,1893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">
<taxonomicName id="4C34B0E3FFD0FF8319EB601551422B44" authorityName="Homrani-Bakali &amp; Susanna" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,340,1795,1821]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltieri">
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF8319EB601551422B44" box="[136,340,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">Centaurea peltieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF8318B0601551FB2B44" box="[467,493,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">C.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C34B0E3FFD0FF831B4F601553542B44" authority="(Cass.) DC." authorityName="DC." baseAuthorityName="Cass." box="[556,834,1795,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Melanoloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF831B4F601552AC2B44" box="[556,698,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">Melanoloma</emphasis>
(Cass.) DC.
</taxonomicName>
and is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C34B0E3FFD0FF831A896015549F2B44" authorityName="Cosson ex Maire" authorityYear="1932" box="[1002,1161,1795,1821]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="takredensis">
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF831A896015549F2B44" box="[1002,1161,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">C. takredensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only species from the section with epappose achenes (
<tableCitation id="C6B6FEDBFFD0FF831889603152392B18" box="[490,559,1831,1857]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparisons of diagnostic characters of species belonging to C. sect. Melanoloma." pageId="1" pageNumber="193">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C34B0E3FFD0FF831B8A6031539E2B18" authorityName="Cosson ex Maire" authorityYear="1932" box="[745,904,1831,1857]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="takredensis">
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF831B8A6031539E2B18" box="[745,904,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">C. takredensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the arachnoid bracts especially above, and the middle bracts ended in a spinescent, pinnate, recurvate appendage (
<figureCitation id="130FD7E5FFD0FF831A19605D53AA2B3C" box="[890,956,1867,1893]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1814,1836]" captionTargetBox="[305,1281,603,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-199@2.[305,1281,603,1755]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Centaurea peltieri. Plant (A), involucral bracts outer (B), middle (C) and inner (D), leave (E), achene (F), capitula (G), outer sterile flower (H), inner fertile flower (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
to 5).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSection id="E2BBD28BFFD0FF8119EB608451CF2B10" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="195" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" type="multiple">
<subSubSection id="C32E98EBFFD0FF8019EB608454902E78" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8BCB60FFD0FF8319EB608451042BF5" blockId="1.[136,1451,1938,2073]" box="[136,274,1938,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">
<heading id="D0C37C0CFFD0FF8319EB608451042BF5" bold="true" box="[136,274,1938,1964]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B9401772FFD0FF8319EB608451042BF5" bold="true" box="[136,274,1938,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8BCB60FFD0FF8019EB60A154902E78" blockId="1.[136,1451,1938,2073]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,545]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="194" pageId="1" pageNumber="193">
Perennial, woolly-tomentose, rosulate multicaulescent herb, stemless (sometimes with peduncles up to 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD0FF831C7560A055442B88" box="[1302,1362,1974,2001]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
), green, unarmed except for the involucral bracts. Base of the stems usually covered with remains of old leaves. Rosette leaves oblong, lyrate-pinnatipartite up to 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD0FF831B3B60E952862440" box="[600,656,2047,2073]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD0FF831A6260E8535B2440" box="[769,845,2046,2073]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="193" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
wide, decreasing in size inwards; margins entire; 1–5 lateral lobes oblong to ovate, terminal lobe ovate-lanceolate, rounded; inner cauline leaves entire, undulate, narrowly lanceolate, pubescent with simple conic trichomes and sessile glands. Capitula solitary in the center of the rosettes, ovoid, 19–30 × 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF80185C67F051AB2D58" box="[319,445,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="20.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="15.0">15–25 mm</quantity>
; outer florets sterile, central ones hermaphrodite; involucral bracts imbricate, apparently arranged in 6–8 rows, greenish or greenish-yellow, gradually increasing in length inwards, inconspicuously blackveined and arachnoid in the upper part; appendages of the middle bracts sericeous, fimbriate, usually reflexed, with a pinnate-spinose apical appendage with 2–12 denticules, terminated in a short spine. Corolla of hermaphrodite florets 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF8019EB666051152DC8" box="[136,259,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="26.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="24.0">24–28 mm</quantity>
long, yellow to yellowish, 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF801B23666052BB2DC8" box="[576,685,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10 mm</quantity>
long, limb 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF801A56666053B72DC8" box="[821,929,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="9.0">9–11 mm</quantity>
long, whitish at the base and yellow towards the apex, with 3–5 lobes, sparsely glandular; stamens with papillose filaments, anthers 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF801D09668C54DE2DEC" box="[1130,1224,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
long, creamy. Style yellowish with stigma branches separated at the apex. Achenes epappose, black to creamy white, 3.1–5 × 
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF801C7D66A855B12D80" box="[1310,1447,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="1.8" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2.1 mm</quantity>
, columnar-ovoid, slightly compressed, elliptical in section, sparsely covered with white hairs (
<quantity id="4CCC6685FFD3FF801DF466F455092DA4" box="[1175,1311,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="194" unit="mm" value="0.15" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.2 mm</quantity>
long) on the faces and with more or less dense hairs around the basal part. Flowering from May to June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
